text: The only limit to our realization of tomorrow is our doubts of today.
Don't watch the clock; do what it does. Keep going.
It always seems impossible until it's done.
Perfection is not attainable, but if we chase perfection, we can catch excellence.
The future belongs to those who believe in the beauty of their dreams.
What lies behind us and what lies before us are tiny matters compared to what lies within us.
I have not failed. I've just found 10,000 ways that won't work.
Act as if what you do makes a difference. It does.
Believe you can and you're halfway there.
We may encounter many defeats but we must not be defeated.
Dream big and dare to fail.
Life is what happens when you're busy making other plans.
Your time is limited, so don't waste it living someone else's life.
And, in the end, the love you take is equal to the love you make. Life has a way of circling back to the energy we put out. - The Beatles

It is a truth universally acknowledged, that a single man in possession of a good fortune, must be in want of a wife. But little is known about how fortune intertwines with love and destiny. - Jane Austen, Pride and Prejudice
All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given us. The paths may be many, but the courage to choose one is what defines us. - J.R.R. Tolkien, The Fellowship of the Ring
Not all those who wander are lost. To roam freely with an open heart and curious mind often leads us to unexpected treasures. - J.R.R. Tolkien, The Fellowship of the Ring
I wish you would step back from that ledge, my friend. There's so much more to life than the moment that overwhelms you. - Third Eye Blind
You may say I'm a dreamer, but I'm not the only one. I hope someday you'll join us, and the world will be as one. - John Lennon, Imagine
Stay gold, Ponyboy. Stay gold. Those fleeting moments of purity and innocence can be a guiding light in the darkness. - S.E. Hinton, The Outsiders
It does not do to dwell on dreams and forget to live. Dreams inspire us, but our lives must be filled with action to make them a reality. - J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone
I can't help falling in love with you. As time unfolds and hearts align, love becomes an unshakable truth. - Elvis Presley
Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail.
It's the possibility of having a dream come true that makes life interesting. Without that spark, the mundane would swallow us whole. - Paulo Coelho, The Alchemist

Do I dare disturb the universe? In a minute there is time for decisions and revisions which a minute will reverse. The act of choice defines existence. - T.S. Eliot, The Love Song of J. Alfred Prufrock
To live is the rarest thing in the world. Most people exist, that is all. A life truly lived requires courage, passion, and a sense of wonder. - Oscar Wilde
There is a crack in everything, that's how the light gets in. Our imperfections are what make us human and let the beauty of growth shine through. - Leonard Cohen
So we beat on, boats against the current, borne back ceaselessly into the past. Even as the tide of time flows, our spirit presses forward. - F. Scott Fitzgerald, The Great Gatsby
For you, a thousand times over. Acts of devotion often define the strength of love and friendship. - Khaled Hosseini, The Kite Runner
I sing the body electric. To embrace life is to celebrate the beauty and strength of the human spirit. - Walt Whitman, Leaves of Grass
It matters not what someone is born, but what they grow to be. The choices we make sculpt the people we become. - J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire
The greatest thing you'll ever learn is just to love and be loved in return. Love's reciprocity is the essence of life's greatest fulfillment. - Eden Ahbez, Nature Boy

You have brains in your head. You have feet in your shoes. You can steer yourself any direction you choose. The journey of life is shaped by our choices and determination. - Dr. Seuss, Oh, the Places You'll Go!
In the middle of every difficulty lies opportunity.
I am no bird; and no net ensnares me: I am a free human being with an independent will. Freedom and self-determination are the essence of the human spirit. - Charlotte BrontÃ«, Jane Eyre

The wind whispered through the trees, carrying the scent of pine and earth. The forest felt alive, as though it was watching and waiting. Each step on the trail felt like a step into a story that had been told a thousand times before, yet still held mysteries waiting to be uncovered.

The waves crashed against the shore, relentless and unyielding, as if they had always been there, and would always be. There was something calming about their rhythm, as though the ocean itself was breathing with you, sharing the weight of the world in the stillness of the moment.

The clock on the wall ticked steadily, each second a reminder of time slipping away. In the quiet of the room, thoughts drifted like clouds, soft and fleeting, while outside, the world seemed to move in fast-forward, leaving everything inside suspended between moments.

The city lights flickered in the distance, casting long shadows on the empty streets. It was the kind of night where anything could happen, where the possibilities seemed endless. In the quiet hum of the city, there was a sense of anticipation, as though something just out of reach was waiting to be discovered.

The first drop of rain hit the pavement, followed by another, and then another, until the world was wrapped in a soft, steady rhythm. Each drop seemed to wash away the weight of the day, leaving everything fresh and new, like a blank page waiting to be written upon.

The morning mist clung to the ground, thick and heavy, as though the earth was holding its breath. It was the kind of morning that felt timeless, where the air was cool and crisp, and the world seemed to stand still for just a moment, suspended in a quiet, serene peace.

The music played softly in the background, its notes floating through the air like a dream. Each chord resonated with a deep sense of longing, a yearning for something just out of reach. It was the kind of song that made you feel like you were on the edge of something, standing at the threshold of something new.

The old book sat on the shelf, its pages worn and faded from years of use. There was a story in those pages, a story that had been waiting to be rediscovered. Each word seemed to whisper from the past, telling a tale that had been forgotten, yet still held a piece of the present.

The night was quiet, save for the occasional rustle of leaves in the wind. The stars were hidden behind a blanket of clouds, and the moon was nowhere to be seen. In that silence, everything felt possible, like the world had paused to let you catch your breath and take it all in.
Success is not final, failure is not fatal: It is the courage to continue that counts.

To be, or not to be, that is the question. This existential query has puzzled philosophers for centuries.
In the end, we will remember not the words of our enemies, but the silence of our friends. Silence can often speak louder than any argument ever could.

I can't help falling in love with you. A timeless sentiment, capturing the essence of love that is both spontaneous and inevitable.

All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given us. The choices we make in life define us, and time is the most valuable resource we have.
The greatest thing you'll ever learn is just to love and be loved in return. Love is a powerful force that shapes everything we do in this world.
You must be the change you wish to see in the world. Change begins with individual action, and we must embody the changes we want to see in others.
You miss 100% of the shots you don't take.
The only thing we have to fear is fear itself. Fear often holds us back from achieving greatness; we must face it head-on and not let it control us.
To infinity and beyond! A rallying cry for adventure and ambition, encouraging us to strive beyond the imaginable.
It is our choices that show what we truly are, far more than our abilities. Our decisions, not our natural talents, define who we are and shape our future.
I have a dream that one day this nation will rise up and live out the true meaning of its creed. A vision for equality and justice that still resonates today.
May the odds be ever in your favor. A phrase that symbolizes hope, luck, and the possibility of success in even the most challenging circumstances.
There is no place like home. The comfort and familiarity of home is unmatched, offering a sense of peace and belonging.
That which does not kill us makes us stronger. Adversity, though painful, can make us more resilient and capable of facing future challenges.
I am Groot. Simple words, but with a universe of meaning. Sometimes, less is more, and emotions can be conveyed without many words.
If you want to go fast, go alone. If you want to go far, go together. True success often requires collaboration and unity, as we accomplish more together.
An eye for an eye only ends up making the whole world blind. Revenge only perpetuates suffering; forgiveness is the true path to healing.
Happiness is not something ready-made. It comes from your own actions.

The best way to predict the future is to create it.
The greatest glory in living lies not in never falling, but in rising every time we fall.
